TopicTitle: [1.1.3] MKS Lite - A lighter, friendlier colonization mod from USI [0.4.4]

Articles.Content:
Just installed MKS-L. a couple of questions I can't find answers to in the forum:

  1. Landing Modular Wheels - how / where do I attach these? I'm trying to play without KIS (using KAS and MKS-L only) and wheels look like the best way to move my base parts around, but can't figure out how to make the wheels work with the Scout lander
  2. Disconnected Bases - RoverDude mentions that these work better and less likely to be eaten by the Kraken. What's a disconnected base?
  3. Anchoring bases - my base demos I've built tend to move around. RoverDude mentioned anchoring pieces, how do I do that?

Thanks for an awesome mod and for help with my questions. Is there a good tutorial / guide out there? I've read the Wiki and this full forum so far.

1 hour ago, tjt said:

Just installed MKS-L. a couple of questions I can't find answers to in the forum:

  1. Landing Modular Wheels - how / where do I attach these? I'm trying to play without KIS (using KAS and MKS-L only) and wheels look like the best way to move my base parts around, but can't figure out how to make the wheels work with the Scout lander
  2. Disconnected Bases - RoverDude mentions that these work better and less likely to be eaten by the Kraken. What's a disconnected base?
  3. Anchoring bases - my base demos I've built tend to move around. RoverDude mentioned anchoring pieces, how do I do that?

Thanks for an awesome mod and for help with my questions. Is there a good tutorial / guide out there? I've read the Wiki and this full forum so far.

Can't answer your first question, but I can answer the second one: Different base modules connected via KAS pipes and crew tubes. As for you're last question, It's better suited for the KAS thread, but there is an inbuilt manual on the different hotkeys and functions of KAS.

1 hour ago, Andem said:

Can't answer your first question, but I can answer the second one: Different base modules connected via KAS pipes and crew tubes. As for you're last question, It's better suited for the KAS thread, but there is an inbuilt manual on the different hotkeys and functions of KAS.

That's wrong - Disconnected is just that: not connected.  By anything.  You put the sections of the base close together (max of 150 meters), and the Kerbals will run around transferring stuff on their own.    (Or maybe they build transfer carts, who knows.  The point is that resources and things like habitation for USI-LS get shared among all the nearby ships.)

On number 3 - If you take on of the parts and attach it to the ground using KIS (I suggest the inflatable hub), then it should be anchored to that spot.  It won't completely prevent it moving around, but it'll help.

I play normal MKS, so I'm not entirely sure what parts are in this pack, but if it's the same mini-wheels, they surface attach.  In MKS there's some girders on the bases in the right places, but I'm not sure those parts are in this pack.

Roverdude, could you walk me though what files I need to grab from MKS and where I should put them so that I can get my EPL survey stations to require material kits and specialized parts instead of the rocket parts it's currently looking for.

Think of the Kerbals! That poor engineer is gonna starve if he can't get his base up and running.
Sure, all you need to do is steal the EL config from the UKS download

The exact file name will be EL_USI.cfg.

As for where you place it - anywhere in GameData should work.

Well that worked. I promise I tried that a few days ago to no avail. I think what was throwing me was I had a build already open awaiting acceptance. I had to cancel it and start another. Then it asked for material kits instead of rocket parts.

You have saved many Kerbal lives today!

Hey Rover,

I had an idea regarding inflatables with crew capacity, but no hatch and rescue contracts.  As an example the mk1 crew cabin, no hatch, but kerbals can eva from it even its the only part after a typical kerbal landing.  It has a crew hatch on the attachment node that allows the kerbal to eva from it.  Hope it helps.

On 4/25/2016 at 8:13 AM, RoverDude said:

Nope, part of CRP.  You can choose to just ignore them tho

You could edit the CRP config file to remove those resources, but you'd need to A: really know what you're doing, and B: Accept that it can (likely will) break any other mod using CRP.  Very much not recommended.

Please don't do that (Edit CRP) as it kinda goes everything CRP stands for.

That was my point - it's really only useful if it's the only mod you're using, it REALLY bothers you, and you know what you're doing and don't plan to post any problems to the mod-maker's thread.  And totally, it goes against the core purpose of CRP.

A question regarding the Scout crusher to get fertilizer from dirt...

I have two dirt drills, an inflatable storage (dirt/ore), fertilizer container and a scout crush-o-matic placed on a lander. When I start the crusher it says "0% efficiency" and will not transform the dirt into fertilizer. There is plenty of dirt and Ec so that should not be a problem. Do you need a scientist/engineer to operate these? I noticed some of the parts list that they need a specialist in the description, but nothing is listed for the crusher.

What am I doing wrong?

 

 

edit: I just made a Karibou with the dril and crusher, and there it wok fine with eng/sci/pilot on board, so I think I need the crew member.
